
# Motor Vibration Monitor (ESP32 + Modbus RTU)

This project implements a multi-node industrial-style vibration monitoring system for bearing condition analysis using ESP32 microcontrollers.

## System Overview

- 5 ESP32 sensor nodes
- 1 ESP32 gateway
- RS-485 / Modbus RTU communication
- Wi-Fi + WebSocket dashboard

## Sensor Node Features

Each node includes:
- ADXL345 accelerometer (primary vibration sensor)
- Piezo sensor (impact/spike detection)
- WS2812 LED (local status indicator)
- MAX485 (RS-485 interface)

Each node performs:
- RMS vibration calculation
- BDU calculation (Bearing Damage Units)
- Threshold comparison (Normal / Warning / Fault)
- Modbus RTU slave communication

## Gateway Features

The gateway:
- polls all 5 nodes via Modbus RTU
- aggregates vibration data
- hosts a web dashboard over Wi-Fi
- streams live updates using WebSockets
- allows threshold updates to nodes

## Vibration Metric

Primary metric:

BDU = 100 × RMS acceleration (g)

## Status States

- NORMAL
- WARNING
- FAULT

